slides.title: 18th century French trade merchandises
slides.text:
data has been extracted from a database built in [the TOFLIT18 project](http://toflit18.hypotheses.org/).  

- nodes are merchandise labels
- edges are hierarchial link between labels

The hierarchy is indicated in sources by a *curly bracket*.
fr : en  
bétail : **cattle**, vaches : **cows**, tuées : **killed**

slides.title: a merchandise hierarchy
slides.text:
The *curly brackets* create a hierarchy of merchandise.  
Here is a hierarchy of music instruments.

The strength of red indicates the minimum level of hierarchy of one node.

**violons** is as red as **instrument**, indicating that one can find it alone in the source.

The *"instrument" { "de musique"* prefix is therefore not used systematically !

slides.title: wines
slides.text:
**vin** is a cluster of merchandises labels precising the origin of production

*Note that the color of nodes changed. Colors indicate now the **modularity class** of the node*

![Source scan](http://medialab.github.io/manylines/ars2015/resources/toflit18.png)

slides.title: Bourgogne
slides.text:
Linked to **de bourgogne** one find a long list of local wine production places

Bourgogne : **Burgundy**

slides.title: More soberly: water
slides.text:
Well actually *eau de vie* means **brandy**

eau : **water**, eau de senteur : **perfume**

slides.title: eau leads to médicinal
slides.text:
One link from *eau* targets *médicinal*.
The water cluster is closed to the biggest cluster of the network : chemicals.
This cluster main labels are :
- drogue : **drugs**
- médicinal : **medicinal**
- chimique : **chemical**
- pour la peinture et la teinture : **paint and dye**

slides.title: gomme and gommes
slides.text:
In this chemical cluster we find **gomme** and **gommes** !

Data have not been cleaned properly...  

But the fact we find those two close one to another validates the temptation to reduce plural forms to their singular version.

gomme : **gum**

slides.title: The main merchandises of our data : fabrics !
slides.text:
This 4 clusters main labels are : 
- in green - *fil* : **thread**
- in purple - *toile* : **hessian**
- in orange - *drap* : **fabric**
- in red - *étoffe* : **cloth material**

The clusters contain many qualifiers about composition or origin of fabrics.
Those qualifiers are the bridges which connect the 4 clusters one with the other.

slides.title: The complete network
slides.text: Feel free to explore the network of 18th century French trade merchandises !
